Lagos – Hapoel Be’er Sheva of Israel midfielder, John Ugochukwu Ogu is not going to take lightly his participation in this month’s international friendly matches lined up for the Super Eagles. Ogu, who had his debut with the Super Eagles in 2013 and has two goals to his credit in his 16 appearances for the team, belives this, is another opportunity to prove a point in the team. “I feel blessed to be called up for the Super Eagles of Nigeria in our upcoming friendly matches. I will never joke with this opportunity and privilege. “It is a privilege to be invited for the two friendly matches and want to use the matches to prove a point,” Ogu said. Three–time African champions, Nigeria will trade tackles with the Bialo-Czerwoni of Poland at the 43,000–capacity Stadium Wroclaw on Friday, March 23, 2018. Four days later, the Super Eagles will take to the pitch against the Senior National Team of Serbia at The Hive, London-home ground of Barnet FC and London Bees. These are the first two in a list of six friendly encounters planned for the Super Eagles by the Nigeria Football Federation ahead of the 21st FIFA World Cup finals in the Russian Federation this summer. 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.